I"b<h4 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h4>
<ul>
  <li>1 pound salted butter, preferably grass-fed</li>
  <li>1/4 cup brown sugar</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon cinnamon (to taste)</li>
  <li>1/2 tsp vanilla extract (optional)</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="steps">Steps</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Let butter soften on counter for a few hours until it’s easy to squish with a fork.</li>
  <li>Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over, and mix until fully integrated. Add vanilla if desired.</li>
  <li>Scoop little teaspoon-size chunks onto a plate and place in freezer for 10 minutes.</li>
  <li>Place the little scoopy chunks into a tupperware in the fridge.</li>
</ol>

<p>Based on <a href="http://wholenaturallife.com/cinnamon-butter-bites-gaps-friendly/">this recipe from wholenaturallife.com</a>, but I hate how it takes like 2 minutes to scroll down to the recipe so I’m duplicating it here.</p>
